{
  "text": "We believe that our results are generalizable to care settings beyond the VA. VA HIV-infected patients are older and have more comorbidities than generally reported. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] However, with the improved outcomes being seen with HIV treatment, the HIV-infected patient population is generally aging and becoming more susceptible to comorbidities, and the VA population may represent the future of the US HIV epidemic in that respect. 40 -42 Except for being overwhelmingly male, the income status and racial/ethnic distribution of HIV-infected veterans is similar to that of many other HIVinfected populations in the US. The median time to viral suppression of our study patients is longer than that reported in modern clinical trials of treatment-naive patients, reflecting the fact that majority of our study patients experienced multiple comorbid conditions and prior failures to respond to treatment.",
